<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">Why? Well, to make a decorated pot, youâ€™ll need either pottery sherds or bricks. Bricks are easy to make, but plain. Pottery sherds are harder to acquire â€“ youâ€™ll need to grab a brush and hunt for archeological remains â€“ but the results are much more beautiful. Either way, youâ€™ll need four in total.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">Place those four into a crafting grid in a diamond pattern and youâ€™ll be rewarded with a decorated pot. But be careful! The side textures of the pot will correspond with what items you put where. If you have one sherd and three bricks, one face will be decorated. Two and two gives two decorated faces, and so on. The one you put in the bottom slot is the one thatâ€™ll face you when you place the pot down, so make that the prettiest</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">Once youâ€™ve made your pot, place it somewhere attractive in your home and go about your business. Every now and then youâ€™ll notice it again and be reminded of the beauty of this world. You can even put a flowerpot on top with a flower in, making it look like the flower is inside the large pot. Isnâ€™t that nice? Time to get rid of it? Just break it to drop the component parts you used to craft it.</Paragraph>
