<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">In Earthâ€™s history, cultures have been making pots and other ceramics for more than 25,000 years but decoration didnâ€™t become common until perhaps 7,000-8,000 years ago, during the Neolithic era.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">Some of the best-known ancient decorated pots come from the â€œred-figureâ€ pottery of the ancient Greeks â€“ where the background is painted black while the figures and other details are left as the natural color of the clay. This innovation swiftly replaced the â€œblack-figureâ€ style that came before it.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">Today, ceramic art is found all over the world in almost every culture. Nearly all of the worldâ€™s ceramics are mass-produced in large factories, but thereâ€™s still a strong tradition of hand-made, small-scale items that are decorated with care and love, and of passing beautiful pieces down the generations.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">So when youâ€™re ready to give up your Minecraft world and start anew, consider passing your most beautiful decorated pots down to a nearby friendly villager. Theyâ€™ll be sure to treasure them as much as you did!</Paragraph>
